{
  "texts": [
    "In the EU, when personal data is processed, the General Data Protection Regulation ('GDPR') is applicable.",
    "If the processing is not lawful, then the provider of the AI might be held liable.",
    "Moreover, if fed with personal data, GenAI can generate personal data in the output (such as real names, addresses), hence make them publicly known.",
    "A proposed solution would be to ensure that the GenAI is 'fed' only with anonymised data and apply data filters that detect and remove personal information from the training data.",
    "As it is incredibly burdensome for the GenAI provider to implement effective mechanisms for checking whether the personal data provided by a user has been lawfully collected, the contractual clauses set forth between the provider and the user are meant to shift the liability from the former to the latter."
  ]
}